42Lk 13:26 "Then you will say, 'We ate and drank with you, and you taught in our streets.'
42Lk 13:27 "But he will reply, 'I don't know you or where you come from. Away from me, all you evildoers!'
42Lk 13:28 "There will be weeping there, and gnashing of teeth, when you see Abraham, Isaac and Jacob and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, but you yourselves thrown out.
42Lk 13:29 People will come from east and west and north and south, and will take their places at the feast in the kingdom of God.
42Lk 13:30 Indeed there are those who are last who will be first, and first who will be last."
42Lk 13:31 At that time some Pharisees came to Jesus and said to him, "Leave this place and go somewhere else. Herod wants to kill you."
42Lk 13:32 He replied, "Go tell that fox, 'I will drive out demons and heal people today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will reach my goal.'
