42Lk 14:15 When one of those at the table with him heard this, he said to Jesus, "Blessed is the man who will eat at the feast in the kingdom of God."
42Lk 14:16 Jesus replied£º "A certain man was preparing a great banquet and invited many guests.
42Lk 14:17 At the time of the banquet he sent his servant to tell those who had been invited, 'Come, for everything is now ready.'
42Lk 14:18 "But they all alike began to make excuses. The first said, 'I have just bought a field, and I must go and see it. Please excuse me.'
42Lk 14:19 "Another said, 'I have just bought five yoke of oxen, and I'm on my way to try them out. Please excuse me.'
42Lk 14:20 "Still another said, 'I just got married, so I can't come.'
42Lk 14:21 "The servant came back and reported this to his master. Then the owner of the house became angry and ordered his servant, 'Go out quickly into the streets and alleys of the town and bring in the poor, the crippled, the blind and the lame.'
42Lk 14:22 "'Sir,' the servant said, 'what you ordered has been done, but there is still room.'
42Lk 14:23 "Then the master told his servant, 'Go out to the roads and country lanes and make them come in, so that my house will be full.
42Lk 14:24 I tell you, not one of those men who were invited will get a taste of my banquet.'"
42Lk 14:25 Large crowds were traveling with Jesus, and turning to them he said£º
42Lk 14:26 "If anyone comes to me and does not hate his father and mother, his wife and children, his brothers and sisters--yes, even his own life--he cannot be my disciple.
42Lk 14:27 And anyone who does not carry his cross and follow me cannot be my disciple.
42Lk 14:28 "Suppose one of you wants to build a tower. Will he not first sit down and estimate the cost to see if he has enough money to complete it?
42Lk 14:29 For if he lays the foundation and is not able to finish it, everyone who sees it will ridicule him,
42Lk 14:30 saying, 'This fellow began to build and was not able to finish.'
42Lk 14:31 "Or suppose a king is about to go to war against another king. Will he not first sit down and consider whether he is able with ten thousand men to oppose the one coming against him with twenty thousand?
42Lk 14:32 If he is not able, he will send a delegation while the other is still a long way off and will ask for terms of peace.
42Lk 14:33 In the same way, any of you who does not give up everything he has cannot be my disciple.
42Lk 14:34 "Salt is good, but if it loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again?
42Lk 14:35 It is fit neither for the soil nor for the manure pile; it is thrown out. "He who has ears to hear, let him hear."
42Lk 15:1 Now the tax collectors and "sinners" were all gathering around to hear him.
42Lk 15:2 But the Pharisees and the teachers of the law muttered, "This man welcomes sinners and eats with them."
42Lk 15:3 Then Jesus told them this parable£º
42Lk 15:4 "Suppose one of you has a hundred sheep and loses one of them. Does he not leave the ninety-nine in the open country and go after the lost sheep until he finds it?
42Lk 15:5 And when he finds it, he joyfully puts it on his shoulders
42Lk 15:6 and goes home. Then he calls his friends and neighbors together and says, 'Rejoice with me; I have found my lost sheep.'
42Lk 15:7 I tell you that in the same way there will be more rejoicing in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need to repent.
42Lk 15:8 "Or suppose a woman has ten silver coins and loses one. Does she not light a lamp, sweep the house and search carefully until she finds it?
42Lk 15:9 And when she finds it, she calls her friends and neighbors together and says, 'Rejoice with me; I have found my lost coin.'
42Lk 15:10 In the same way, I tell you, there is rejoicing in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents."
42Lk 15:11 Jesus continued£º "There was a man who had two sons.
42Lk 15:12 The younger one said to his father, 'Father, give me my share of the estate.' So he divided his property between them.
42Lk 15:13 "Not long after that, the younger son got together all he had, set off for a distant country and there squandered his wealth in wild living.
42Lk 15:14 After he had spent everything, there was a severe famine in that whole country, and he began to be in need.
42Lk 15:15 So he went and hired himself out to a citizen of that country, who sent him to his fields to feed pigs.
42Lk 15:16 He longed to fill his stomach with the pods that the pigs were eating, but no one gave him anything.
42Lk 15:17 "When he came to his senses, he said, 'How many of my father's hired men have food to spare, and here I am starving to death!
42Lk 15:18 I will set out and go back to my father and say to him£º Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you.
42Lk 15:19 I am no longer worthy to be called your son; make me like one of your hired men.'
42Lk 15:20 So he got up and went to his father. "But while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and was filled with compassion for him; he ran to his son, threw his arms around him and kissed him.
42Lk 15:21 "The son said to him, 'Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you. I am no longer worthy to be called your son.'
42Lk 15:22 "But the father said to his servants, 'Quick! Bring the best robe and put it on him. Put a ring on his finger and sandals on his feet.
42Lk 15:23 Bring the fattened calf and kill it. Let's have a feast and celebrate.
42Lk 15:24 For this son of mine was dead and is alive again; he was lost and is found.' So they began to celebrate.
42Lk 15:25 "Meanwhile, the older son was in the field. When he came near the house, he heard music and dancing.
42Lk 15:26 So he called one of the servants and asked him what was going on.
42Lk 15:27 'Your brother has come,' he replied, 'and your father has killed the fattened calf because he has him back safe and sound.'
42Lk 15:28 "The older brother became angry and refused to go in. So his father went out and pleaded with him.
42Lk 15:29 But he answered his father, 'Look! All these years I've been slaving for you and never disobeyed your orders. Yet you never gave me even a young goat so I could celebrate with my friends.
42Lk 15:30 But when this son of yours who has squandered your property with prostitutes comes home, you kill the fattened calf for him!'
42Lk 15:31 "'My son,' the father said, 'you are always with me, and everything I have is yours.
42Lk 15:32 But we had to celebrate and be glad, because this brother of yours was dead and is alive again; he was lost and is found.'"
42Lk 16:1 Jesus told his disciples£º "There was a rich man whose manager was accused of wasting his possessions.
42Lk 16:2 So he called him in and asked him, 'What is this I hear about you? Give an account of your management, because you cannot be manager any longer.'
42Lk 16:3 "The manager said to himself, 'What shall I do now? My master is taking away my job. I'm not strong enough to dig, and I'm ashamed to beg--
42Lk 16:4 I know what I'll do so that, when I lose my job here, people will welcome me into their houses.'
42Lk 16:5 "So he called in each one of his master's debtors. He asked the first, 'How much do you owe my master?'
42Lk 16:6 "'Eight hundred gallons of olive oil,' he replied. "The manager told him, 'Take your bill, sit down quickly, and make it four hundred.'
42Lk 16:7 "Then he asked the second, 'And how much do you owe?' "'A thousand bushels of wheat,' he replied. "He told him, 'Take your bill and make it eight hundred.'
42Lk 16:8 "The master commended the dishonest manager because he had acted shrewdly. For the people of this world are more shrewd in dealing with their own kind than are the people of the light.
42Lk 16:9 I tell you, use worldly wealth to gain friends for yourselves, so that when it is gone, you will be welcomed into eternal dwellings.
42Lk 16:10 "Whoever can be trusted with very little can also be trusted with much, and whoever is dishonest with very little will also be dishonest with much.
42Lk 16:11 So if you have not been trustworthy in handling worldly wealth, who will trust you with true riches?
42Lk 16:12 And if you have not been trustworthy with someone else's property, who will give you property of your own?
42Lk 16:13 "No servant can serve two masters. Either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and Money."
42Lk 16:14 The Pharisees, who loved money, heard all this and were sneering at Jesus.
42Lk 16:15 He said to them, "You are the ones who justify yourselves in the eyes of men, but God knows your hearts. What is highly valued among men is detestable in God's sight.
42Lk 16:16 "The Law and the Prophets were proclaimed until John. Since that time, the good news of the kingdom of God is being preached, and everyone is forcing his way into it.
42Lk 16:17 It is easier for heaven and earth to disappear than for the least stroke of a pen to drop out of the Law.
42Lk 16:18 "Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another woman commits adultery, and the man who marries a divorced woman commits adultery.
42Lk 16:19 "There was a rich man who was dressed in purple and fine linen and lived in luxury every day.
42Lk 16:20 At his gate was laid a beggar named Lazarus, covered with sores
42Lk 16:21 and longing to eat what fell from the rich man's table. Even the dogs came and licked his sores.
42Lk 16:22 "The time came when the beggar died and the angels carried him to Abraham's side. The rich man also died and was buried.
42Lk 16:23 In hell, where he was in torment, he looked up and saw Abraham far away, with Lazarus by his side.
42Lk 16:24 So he called to him, 'Father Abraham, have pity on me and send Lazarus to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue, because I am in agony in this fire.'
42Lk 16:25 "But Abraham replied, 'Son, remember that in your lifetime you received your good things, while Lazarus received bad things, but now he is comforted here and you are in agony.
42Lk 16:26 And besides all this, between us and you a great chasm has been fixed, so that those who want to go from here to you cannot, nor can anyone cross over from there to us.'
42Lk 16:27 "He answered, 'Then I beg you, father, send Lazarus to my father's house,
42Lk 16:28 for I have five brothers. Let him warn them, so that they will not also come to this place of torment.'
42Lk 16:29 "Abraham replied, 'They have Moses and the Prophets; let them listen to them.'
42Lk 16:30 "'No, father Abraham,' he said, 'but if someone from the dead goes to them, they will repent.'
42Lk 16:31 "He said to him, 'If they do not listen to Moses and the Prophets, they will not be convinced even if someone rises from the dead.'"
42Lk 17:1 Jesus said to his disciples£º "Things that cause people to sin are bound to come, but woe to that person through whom they come.
42Lk 17:2 It would be better for him to be thrown into the sea with a millstone tied around his neck than for him to cause one of these little ones to sin.
42Lk 17:3 So watch yourselves. "If your brother sins, rebuke him, and if he repents, forgive him.
42Lk 17:4 If he sins against you seven times in a day, and seven times comes back to you and says, 'I repent,' forgive him."
42Lk 17:5 The apostles said to the Lord, "Increase our faith!"
42Lk 17:6 He replied, "If you have faith as small as a mustard seed, you can say to this mulberry tree, 'Be uprooted and planted in the sea,' and it will obey you.
42Lk 17:7 "Suppose one of you had a servant plowing or looking after the sheep. Would he say to the servant when he comes in from the field, 'Come along now and sit down to eat'?
42Lk 17:8 Would he not rather say, 'Prepare my supper, get yourself ready and wait on me while I eat and drink; after that you may eat and drink'?
42Lk 17:9 Would he thank the servant because he did what he was told to do?
