42Lk 24:17 He asked them, "What are you discussing together as you walk along?" They stood still, their faces downcast.
42Lk 24:18 One of them, named Cleopas, asked him, "Are you only a visitor to Jerusalem and do not know the things that have happened there in these days?"
42Lk 24:19 "What things?" he asked. "About Jesus of Nazareth," they replied. "He was a prophet, powerful in word and deed before God and all the people.
42Lk 24:20 The chief priests and our rulers handed him over to be sentenced to death, and they crucified him;
42Lk 24:21 but we had hoped that he was the one who was going to redeem Israel. And what is more, it is the third day since all this took place.
42Lk 24:22 In addition, some of our women amazed us. They went to the tomb early this morning
42Lk 24:23 but didn't find his body. They came and told us that they had seen a vision of angels, who said he was alive.
42Lk 24:24 Then some of our companions went to the tomb and found it just as the women had said, but him they did not see."
42Lk 24:25 He said to them, "How foolish you are, and how slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken!
42Lk 24:26 Did not the Christ have to suffer these things and then enter his glory?"
42Lk 24:27 And beginning with Moses and all the Prophets, he explained to them what was said in all the Scriptures concerning himself.
42Lk 24:28 As they approached the village to which they were going, Jesus acted as if he were going farther.
42Lk 24:29 But they urged him strongly, "Stay with us, for it is nearly evening; the day is almost over." So he went in to stay with them.
42Lk 24:30 When he was at the table with them, he took bread, gave thanks, broke it and began to give it to them.
42Lk 24:31 Then their eyes were opened and they recognized him, and he disappeared from their sight.
42Lk 24:32 They asked each other, "Were not our hearts burning within us while he talked with us on the road and opened the Scriptures to us?"
42Lk 24:33 They got up and returned at once to Jerusalem. There they found the Eleven and those with them, assembled together
42Lk 24:34 and saying, "It is true! The Lord has risen and has appeared to Simon."
42Lk 24:35 Then the two told what had happened on the way, and how Jesus was recognized by them when he broke the bread.
42Lk 24:36 While they were still talking about this, Jesus himself stood among them and said to them, "Peace be with you."
42Lk 24:37 They were startled and frightened, thinking they saw a ghost.
42Lk 24:38 He said to them, "Why are you troubled, and why do doubts rise in your minds?
42Lk 24:39 Look at my hands and my feet. It is I myself! Touch me and see; a ghost does not have flesh and bones, as you see I have."
42Lk 24:40 When he had said this, he showed them his hands and feet.
42Lk 24:41 And while they still did not believe it because of joy and amazement, he asked them, "Do you have anything here to eat?"
42Lk 24:42 They gave him a piece of broiled fish,
42Lk 24:43 and he took it and ate it in their presence.
42Lk 24:44 He said to them, "This is what I told you while I was still with you£º Everything must be fulfilled that is written about me in the Law of Moses, the Prophets and the Psalms."
42Lk 24:45 Then he opened their minds so they could understand the Scriptures.
42Lk 24:46 He told them, "This is what is written£º The Christ will suffer and rise from the dead on the third day,
42Lk 24:47 and repentance and forgiveness of sins will be preached in his name to all nations, beginning at Jerusalem.
42Lk 24:48 You are witnesses of these things.
42Lk 24:49 I am going to send you what my Father has promised; but stay in the city until you have been clothed with power from on high."
42Lk 24:50 When he had led them out to the vicinity of Bethany, he lifted up his hands and blessed them.
42Lk 24:51 While he was blessing them, he left them and was taken up into heaven.
42Lk 24:52 Then they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy.
42Lk 24:53 And they stayed continually at the temple, praising God.
